      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_6",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Honest little runabout with plenty of life left for the right buyer. It\u2019s not perfect and could use some TLC, but it starts, moves, and could make a great budget commuter, project, or handy spare vehicle. If you\u2019re after something affordable and don\u2019t mind putting in a bit of work, this could be a really worthwhile buy. Priced to sell and open to sensible interest.",
      "price": 4900.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Solid project car with great bones and a surprisingly stout powertrain feel. Starts up, moves under its own power, and offers the kind of analog driving character enthusiasts appreciate. Engine bay presents as complete, drivetrain feels usable, and the chassis is a worthwhile foundation for a budget build, weekend wrenching project, or parts saver. Cosmetically rough and will need attention, but that\u2019s reflected in the ask. If you want an affordable platform with real potential and no-nonsense mechanical upside, this is a compelling buy.",
